    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_6787379" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/6787379" />
    <a title="Mark" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/348966-mark"><img alt="Mark" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1189283772p2/348966.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/6787379?book_show_action=true">Sep 25, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mark" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mark" href="/user/show/348966-mark">Mark</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">girls and boys who like their porridge just right</span></div>

        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/348966-mark?shelf=recentlyread">recentlyread</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer6787379" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer430794795047337306">Jack Spratt and his NCD (Nursery Crime Division) team must solve the murder of Goldilocks (in a politically-sensitive modern climate of bear activism and rampant ursism) while tracking down the escaped psycho-killer known as the Ginger Bread Man, all while Jack is under suspension and being outed as a PDR (a person of dubious reality) himself. Jack has a great new car he bought from dealer Dorian Gray that instantly repairs itself--as long as a certain painting remains intact.... Also not to be </span>
  <span id="freeText430794795047337306" style="display:none">Jack Spratt and his NCD (Nursery Crime Division) team must solve the murder of Goldilocks (in a politically-sensitive modern climate of bear activism and rampant ursism) while tracking down the escaped psycho-killer known as the Ginger Bread Man, all while Jack is under suspension and being outed as a PDR (a person of dubious reality) himself. Jack has a great new car he bought from dealer Dorian Gray that instantly repairs itself--as long as a certain painting remains intact.... Also not to be missed: "Somme World," a new theme park that simulates the experience of being in the trenches during one of WWI's most pointless and costly battles. Fun for the whole family! (On a personal note, last year when I had my Satire class read "The Well of Lost Plots," some of the students decided that Jasper Fforde looked like me, ergo I might actually be Jasper Fforde. Can I just say, I'd have no objections to that at all! Who has more fun with literature than Jasper Fforde, I ask you?)</span>
  <a data-text-id="430794795047337306" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
